body: Still not able to build, even with openvino_2020.4.287.

openvino 2020.4 is not yet supported,
but 2020.3 should work. will ping some folks from Intel to see if they have any idea.

Hi @oliveirara, I tried the build on Centos 7 and it worked fine for me. My gcc version was 7.3 and cmake version is 3.18.0. 

Could you please try this configuration and let me know if it works ? 
To install gcc 7.3 without disturbing your 5.3 configuration, you can follow these steps:

$sudo yum install centos-release-scl-rh
$sudo yum install devtoolset-7-toolchain
$ scl enable devtoolset-7 bash

Hi @oliveirara, Could you please test it out with openvino 2020.4 ? We have not been able to reproduce this error with either 2020.3 or 2020.4.

Hi @suryasidd , 

I tried with openvino 2020.4.287, and still have this problem. I believe that this issue is related to linking problems with openvino libraries. 

Most of the errors are like this: 

`onnxruntime/core/providers/openvino/contexts.h:12: undefined reference to `InferenceEngine::Core::`

Maybe if I set up manually the path to openvino libraries inside onnxruntime/core/providers/openvino should in principle solve this problem.

I runned before build onnxruntime source <path-to-openvino>/bin/setupvars.sh, as usual.

Hi @suryasidd, I installed CentOS 7 on a virtual machine and I successfully built OnnxRuntime with OpenVINO 2020.04 (using devtoolset-7, as you mentioned earlier)! I also tested on devtoolset-9 which didn't work (errors appeared while building), and I also built successfully (just to check) on Ubuntu 18.04 LTS (virtual machine). Thank you for your attention 👍
